<br>
Black smithing is one of the most extreme of the tradeskills though, most aren't quite so bad, but still pretty bad.  That being the case, most people figure that they have the right to ask what ever they wish in exchange for their services.  I find it hard to fault them that, although I wouldn't have agreed to the price he asked.<br>
<br>
I'm sure though that you'll find another trades person willing to do the combines for you for a less extreme price.  If there anything trades people have in common, its a difference of opinion on how combines for others should be dealt with.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>The Man in Black: We are men of action, lies do not become us. <br>
